<p>More than 50,000 people answered the call: <a href="https://forum.generationequality.org/actforequal" target="_blank">act for equal</a>. They committed to do all they can to gear up action to achieve the landmark 1995 Beijing Platform for Action, agreed at the Fourth World Conference on Women. The mobilizing force was the <a href="https://nam10.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D85UyyrwflVo&amp;data=04%7C01%7Ccarlotta.aiello%40unwomen.org%7C699ee0a49ef04aa7adb308da1bf59e77%7C2bcd07449e18487d85c3c9a325220be8%7C0%7C0%7C637853038979718671%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000&amp;sdata=%2FPjstIfwgn%2BNzhZj3VvWXXyxj42zFqR09kCcNO%2FnZJw%3D&amp;reserved=0" target="_blank">Generation Equality Forum</a>, a UN Women-orchestrated two-year rally for the rights of women and girls, culminating in events in Mexico City and Paris in 2021. Feminists and advocates, across generations, came to have their say and plan their moves. Heads of State and Government attended, signalling powerful political commitment, as did corporate leaders and heads of philanthropies, cultural and social influencers, and prominent people from across the United Nations. Young activists laid down their challenge: ‚ÄúAre you ready to unite behind the young feminist agenda? Because we now demand real, substantive impact.‚Äù</p>

<p>The Forum galvanized diverse participants to make <a href="https://commitments.generationequality.org/dashboard/directory/" target="_blank">1,000 commitments</a> to ambitious actions to achieve gender equality. They announced an extraordinary USD 40 billion in financial investments to set rapid progress in motion. Participants had a chance to co-create a Global Acceleration Plan. People from every region of the world shared their ideas, such as <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HSZmZ8AwfbM" target="_blank">youth from Europe and Central Asia</a>, activists of <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NA4hWdl80-M&amp;list=PLix6UiDjTOFo-gb_EaXRMEjoF4svXFqC6&amp;index=27" target="_blank">Generation Equality Africa</a> and musicians from <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ciMMqCd9p2U&amp;list=PL_KcKFxi0uV-cvzirKw8fMrY-Z0WsHEuJ" target="_blank">Latin America and the Caribbean</a>.</p>

<p>Now, commitment-makers are acting on their promises. Catalysed by UN Women, <a href="https://forum.generationequality.org/action-coalitions" target="_blank">action coalitions</a> are propelling progress on <a href="https://commitments.generationequality.org/dashboard/directory/" target="_blank">issues core to gender equality</a>, from bodily autonomy, to unpaid care, to economic justice. A new Compact on Women, Peace and Security and Humanitarian Action has nearly 160 signatories. They are funding women leaders to <a href="https://wpshacompact.org/from-victims-to-leaders-ending-gender-based-violence-in-the-lake-chad-basin/" target="_blank">bring peace to troubled communities</a> in the Lake Chad basin, advocating for <a href="https://wpshacompact.org/if-we-truly-want-gender-equality-we-need-to-finance-it/" target="_blank">scaled-up finance</a>, and pressing the Security Council and governments to make good on <a href="https://wpshacompact.org/compact-commemorates-anniversary-of-resolution-1325-on-women-peace-and-security/">existing (and long overdue) commitments</a> to women, peace and security.</p>
